<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=14778&amp;p=178921#p178921"><![CDATA[
phpBB already supports adding arbitrary text fields in Users and Groups &gt; Custom Profile Fields, and an RDF URL field could be put there. But you're correct that at least a <a href="https://www.phpbb.com/mods/" class="postlink">phpBB MOD</a> would be needed to interpret RDF in XML or Turtle format. There are <a href="https://www.phpbb.com/customise/db/extensions-36" class="postlink">190 extensions</a>, but either none of them relate to RDF or the site rejects search terms shorter than four letters.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Sep 04, 2016 2:01 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
