<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=14778&amp;p=178910#p178910"><![CDATA[
Please add a field into the user profile to link to a RDF profile. This way, any user can add their own fields, such as IRC nicknames, etc. It would also be good if during registration it can automatically extract any fields that this forum does support from the RDF profile if one is provided, but it would be OK even if you do not want to bother with programming such thing. (If OpenID login is ever added, then it can also take that from the RDF profile too.)<br /><br />(As an example, my RDF profile (a bit old) is <a href="http://zzo38computer.org/my_foaf.ttl" class="postlink">http://zzo38computer.org/my_foaf.ttl</a>)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4734">zzo38</a> — Sun Sep 04, 2016 11:22 am</p><hr />
